ght raising of both forefingers simultaneously.<ref name=VT39/>\n\n==Etymology==\n[[Magnus Åberg]] has theorized that the word ''iglishmêk'' is composed of *''<nowiki>'</nowiki>igal'' (*\"language\", as in ''aglâb'') and *''shimak'' (*\"gesture\").<ref>{{webcite|author=[[Magnus Åberg]]|articleurl=https://www.forodrim.org/daeron/md_khuzdul.html|articlename=An analysis of Dwarvish|dated=|website=Forod|accessed=1 April 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Inspiration==\nThe concept of communication by signs used by non-deaf users is very similar to the [[Wikipedia:Monastic sign languages|monastic sign languages]] created by [[Christianity|Christian]] monks in order to keep mandatory or voluntary silence.\n\n{{References}}\n\n{{languages}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Iglishmek}}\n[[Category:Khuzdul words]]\n[[Category:Khuzdul]]"}}}